# Chorus patch registry — review routing
#
# Syntax reference: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Policy mirrors `packages/registry/src/reputation.ts:SENSITIVE_SCOPES`.
# Two-maintainer approval is ENFORCED by the branch-protection rule, not by this file alone.
# This file routes; the branch rule decides the count.
#
# Replace the placeholder teams below with real GitHub team/user handles before enabling.

# Default: any change needs at least one of the core maintainers.
*                                       @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers

# Trust-set changes are ALWAYS sensitive.
/trusted-signers.json                   @YOUR_ORG/chorus-security @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers
/revoked.json                           @YOUR_ORG/chorus-security @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers

# CI workflows — touching these grants new signing powers.
/.github/workflows/                     @YOUR_ORG/chorus-security @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers

# Sensitive integration scopes — any patch touching auth/secrets/network must
# have two approvals. GitHub branch protection requires the intersection of these
# groups (security + maintainers) to approve.
#
# NOTE: CODEOWNERS can't match on JSON content (scope fields), so we err on the
# side of routing entire integrations that are known-sensitive. For a broader
# enforcement, `sign-patch.yml` parses the manifest and fails the check if a
# sensitive scope is set without a "security-approved" label from 2 reviewers.
/patches/slack-send/                    @YOUR_ORG/chorus-security @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers
/patches/http-generic/                  @YOUR_ORG/chorus-security @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers

# Docs-only changes: any maintainer can merge.
/README.md                              @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers
/CONTRIBUTING.md                        @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers
/patches/README.md                      @YOUR_ORG/chorus-maintainers
